definition:
ἐπ-άνω 
 adv., [in LXX for מַעֲלָה, עַל, מֵעָל, etc. ;] 
above; 
   1. adverbially; 
   (a) of place: Luk.11:44; 
   (b) of number, more than: Mrk.14:5, 1Co.15:6. 
   2. As prep. C. genitive; 
   (a) of place: Mat.2:9 5:14 21:7 23:18-22 27:37 28:2, Luk.4:39 10:19, Rev.6:8 20:3; 
   (b) of pre-eminence: Luk.19:17-19, Jhn.3:31.†
 (AS)
